    {
      "id": "jaoe38c1lsd94eth",
      "questionNumber": 2,
      "questionText": "<p>The correct order of reactivity in electrophilic substitution reaction of the following compounds is :</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1lse4t284/69192e92-8387-4880-ba07-2aaeedc7ef27/725c4b50-c701-11ee-be30-496b1c29fc5a/file-6y3zli1lse4t285.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1lse4t284/69192e92-8387-4880-ba07-2aaeedc7ef27/725c4b50-c701-11ee-be30-496b1c29fc5a/file-6y3zli1lse4t285.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"JEE Main 2024 (Online) 31st January Evening Shift Chemistry - Basics of Organic Chemistry Question 102 English\"></p>",
      "options": [
        "B > C > A > D",
        "B > A > C > D",
        "D > C > B > A",
        "A > B > C > D"
      ],
      "correctOption": 1,
      "correctAnswer": null,
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Chemistry",
      "topic": "electron-displacement-effect",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "<p>$$-\\mathrm{CH}_3$$ shows $$+\\mathrm{M}$$ and $$+\\mathrm{I}$$.</p>\n<p>$$-\\mathrm{Cl}$$ shows $$+\\mathrm{M}$$ and $$-\\mathrm{I}$$ but inductive effect dominates.</p>\n<p>$$-\\mathrm{NO}_2$$ shows $$-\\mathrm{M}$$ and $$-\\mathrm{I}$$.</p>\n<p>Electrophilic substitution $$\\alpha \\frac{1}{-\\mathrm{M} \\text { and }-\\mathrm{I}}$$</p>\n<p>$$\\alpha+\\mathrm{M} \\text { and }+\\mathrm{I}$$</p>\n<p>Hence, order is $$\\mathrm{B}>\\mathrm{A}>\\mathrm{C}>\\mathrm{D}$$.</p>",
      "section": "A",
      "instruction": "",
      "examSource": "jee-main"
    },
    {
      "id": "ml818ggf",
      "questionNumber": 3,
      "questionText": "<p><b>Identify the correct statements :</b></p><p>The presence of &ndash;NO<sub>2</sub> group in benzene ring</p><p>A. activates the ring towards electrophilic substitutions.</p><p>B. deactivates the ring towards electrophilic substitutions.</p><p>C. activates the ring towards nucleophilic substitutions.</p><p>D. deactivates the ring towards nucleophilic substitutions.</p><p>Choose the correct answer from the options given below :</p>",
      "options": [
        "<p>A and D Only</p>",
        "<p>B and D Only</p>",
        "<p>C and A Only</p>",
        "<p>B and C Only</p>"
      ],
      "correctOption": 3,
      "correctAnswer": null,
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Chemistry",
      "topic": "electron-displacement-effect",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "<p>Presence of $\\mathrm{NO}_2$ group on the benzene ring <b>deactivates</b> the ring towards electrophilic substitution reactions because it shows <b>$-M$ effect</b> (it withdraws electrons from the ring by resonance).</p>\n<p>Because the $\\mathrm{NO}_2$ group pulls electron density away, the ring becomes less reactive towards electrophiles.</p>\n<p>At the same time, the $\\mathrm{NO}_2$ group <b>activates</b> the ring towards nucleophilic substitution because the withdrawal of electrons makes the ring more suitable for attack by nucleophiles (electron-rich species).</p>\n<p>Ans. $\\rightarrow $ B &amp; C</p>",
      "section": "A",
      "instruction": "",
      "examSource": "jee-main"
    },
